Simply put, this is a terrific interactive app and your kids will LOVE it. My 3 year old laughs, claps, has a BLAST-  best of all, she can do everything herself.  So no frustration for her and no worries for me that she will accidentally stray into another territory of my Xoom if I step away. There's SO much to do- Change the CD's in the family room for a different music mood throughout the house.  (I think there are 5 charming background tunes.)  Make coffee, fry up some eggs, take a shower (don't forget to close the shower curtain!) The interactive qualities of this game are endless, making it a tireless favorite for my three year old- and even my 8 year old.  While overall educational value is low, it encourages creative play, and it is a life saver in those times when I am held up unexpectedly with one or both girls and need to keep them entertained; or my little one is getting grouchy when errands are running long.  This app is definitely worth the price tag.  If only there were more out there for which I could say the same! Thanks a bundle, Shimon Young, this is the best Children's android app I've found, and it should be rated much higher.  It's an unsung hero!
